    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "narration_text": "CAR-T achieves 70 to 90 percent complete response in relapsed pediatric B-cell leukemia \u2014 a disease that was once terminal. The same engineering approach barely registers response rates in lung, breast, or pancreatic cancer. The cells are built the same way. The problem is entirely in what they face when they arrive.",
